  "timeframe": "1D / 5M",
  "market_context": "ES daily chart on Friday 11 Aug 2023. Tuesday formed the high of the week, with Wednesday-Thursday expansion lower taking out a daily swing low. Analyst anticipated a TGIF setup retracing 20-30% of the weekly range back into the body.",
  "key_observation": "On the 5-minute, multiple failure swings rest above current price along with the daily open, providing a clear upside draw on liquidity. A sweep and displacement higher set up a New York reversal long opportunity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, identify Tuesday as the weekly high and Wednesday-Thursday expansion taking out the daily swing low, completing the weekly objective.",
    "Step 2: Anticipate a TGIF retracement back into the weekly range and drop to the 5-minute time frame.",
    "Step 3: Mark the daily open on the 5-minute and anticipate a New York reversal higher.",
    "Step 4: Identify multiple failure swings above current price as upside targets along with the daily open.",
    "Step 5: Observe the sweep of the low followed by displacement higher on the 5-minute.",
    "Step 6: Project a standard deviation from the recent high to low upward; note the -2 to -2.5 level aligns just above the failure swings, confirming conviction.",
    "Step 7: Wait for price to close over the prior highs to confirm the shift.",
    "Step 8: Draw a Fibonacci from the new low to the current high, tracking it as price puts in new highs to define the OTE.",
    "Step 9: Enter at the 0.62 OTE level (preferring 0.705 but taking 0.62 to ensure entry), with target at the failure swing highs for a 3.4R trade."
  ],
  "outcome": "Entry triggered; price swept back to the midpoint of the OTE, formed a fair value gap entry, then displaced higher, eventually sweeping the failure swing highs after the daily open provided some resistance. 3.4R trade achieved.",
  "lessons": "Combining a higher-time-frame weekly profile (TGIF) with lower-time-frame OTE entries provides high-conviction setups. Aligning standard deviation projections with failure swing targets reinforces the draw on liquidity and supports trade location.",
